The 33rd Air Base

The 33. Baza Lotnicza, as it is known in its native tongue, stands as a critical strategic asset nestled near the unassuming town of [Powidz](/Powidz) within [Słupca County](/S%C5%82upca_County), in the heart of [Poland](/Poland). This facility, far from being a mere airstrip, represents a nexus of national defense and international cooperation, operating under the vigilant gaze of the [Ministry of National Defence](/Ministry_of_National_Defence_(Poland)) and commanded by the capable hands of the [Polish Air Force](/Polish_Air_Force).

